currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: doing the exact same things without having to lift a finger.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: doing the exact same things without having to lift a finger.

currentSuggestions.original: allowing you to do anything you want while enjoying a full length book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: allowing you to do anything you want while enjoying a full length book.

currentSuggestions.original: expanding your horizons, as you would be exposed to new ideas and a new world.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: expanding your horizons, as you would be exposed to new ideas and a new world.

currentSuggestions.original: helping you become more multi-lingual and increasing how quickly you can listen to a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: helping you become more multi-lingual and increasing how quickly you can listen to a book.

ops.insert: allowing you to do anything you want while enjoying a full length book.

currentSuggestions.original: I think that listening to an audiobook can be just as good as reading a book, but I think reading a book has a few more
